fm: void CombinationPar(vector<string>& result, string& sample, 	                    int deep, int n, int leftNum, int rightNum) 	{ 		if (deep == 2 * n) 		{ 			result.push_back(sample); 			return; 		} 		if (leftNum < n) 		{ 			sample.push_back('('); 			CombinationPar( 			    result, sample, deep + 1, n, leftNum + 1, rightNum); 			sample.resize(sample.size() - 1); 		} 		if (rightNum < leftNum) 		{ 			sample.push_back(')'); 			CombinationPar( 			    result, sample, deep + 1, n, leftNum, rightNum + 1); 			sample.resize(sample.size() - 1); 		} 	}

fm: vector<int> grayCode(int n) { 		vector<int> result; 		result.push_back(0); 		for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) 		{ 			int highestBit = 1 << i; 			int len = result.size(); 			for (int i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--) 			{ 				result.push_back(highestBit + result[i]); 			} 		} 		return result; 	}

fm: int hIndex(vector<int>& citations) {         int start = 0, end = citations.size()-1;                  int max_h = 0;         while(start<=end) {             int mid = start + (end - start)/2;             int h = citations.size() - mid;             if(h<= citations[mid]) {                 end = mid -1;                 max_h = h;             } else {                 start = mid +1;             }         }                  return max_h;     }

fc: class Solution { public: 	char *strStr(char *haystack, char *needle) { 		if (haystack == NULL || needle == NULL) return NULL; 		int hlen = strlen(haystack); 		int nlen = strlen(needle); 		if (nlen == 0) return haystack; 		if (hlen == 0 ) return NULL; 		int pattern[100000]; 		GeneratePattern(needle, nlen, pattern); 		return Match(haystack, needle, pattern); 	}  	void GeneratePattern(char* str, int len, int* pattern) 	{ 		pattern[0] = -1; 		int k = -1; 		for (int j = 1; j < len; j++) 		{ 			while (k > -1 && str[k + 1] != str[j]) 				k = pattern[k]; 			if (str[k + 1] == str[j]) 				k++; 			pattern[j] = k; 		} 	}  	char* Match(char* haystack, char* needle, int* pattern) 	{ 		int hlen = strlen(haystack); 		int nlen = strlen(needle); 		int k = -1; 		for (int j = 0; j < hlen; j++, haystack++) 		{ 			while (k > -1 && needle[k + 1] != *haystack) 				k = pattern[k]; 			if (needle[k + 1] == *haystack) 				k++; 			if (k == nlen - 1) 				return haystack - k; 		} 		return NULL; 	} };
